text_1:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
text_2:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 2.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 3.Following more than a month of Turkish–Armenian War, the Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol is concluded.
 4.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 5.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
 2.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 3.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 4.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
 5.President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.

 The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.

Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.

text_1:
Throughout history the following happened on the day 12/3:
 1.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 2.The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
 3.Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
 4.President Herbert Hoover presents a written message as his first State of the Union message to Congress rather than a speech.
 5.Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

President Herbert Hoover delivers his first State of the Union message to Congress. It is presented in the form of a written message rather than a speech.
The Turkish-dictated Treaty of Alexandropol concluded after a month of Turkish–Armenian War.
Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 Archduke John of Austria was defeated by French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
The current flag of Singapore is adopted, six months after Singapore became self-governing within the British Empire.
Berengar I of Italy was crowned Emperor by Pope John X.
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.

 1.Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
 2.Illinois becomes the 21st U.S. state.
 3.USS Alfred becomes the first vessel to fly the Grand Union Flag; the flag is hoisted by John Paul Jones.
 4.Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
 5.French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden.
text_2:
This happened on the day December 3rd in history: 
 John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor

 John Paul Jones hoisted the the Grand Union Flag on USS Alfred, the first vessel to fly Grand Union Flag.
Singapore adopts it current flag six months after it self-govern within the British Empire.
French General Jean Victor Marie Moreau decisively defeats the Archduke John of Austria near Munich in the Battle of Hohenlinden. 
Illinois joined U.S. as its 21st state.
Pope John X crowns Berengar I of Italy as Holy Roman Emperor
